               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]]: 154 translates: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a1 To let the fore-arm fall [dow] to the navel ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a2 Also very much as you like ... is to be poured [out] &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a3 He does not meet the rules, therefore in this measure ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a4 In the power of ...: Through ... [is] these days &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a5 Look there at this female elephant! Four days ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a6 to let the fore-arm fall [down] from the ... to the navel. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b1 ... the fire of the body changed ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 Seek to know the peculiarities thereof! &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b3 In consequence of this knowledge becomes apparent. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b4 Mix it with the fire-element! [Mix it with] the earth-(element) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b5 Mix it with the water-element! These elements ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b6 Having made ... the brahmaloka-body ... &lt;/p&gt;</item>
